          <!-- THEORY / EXPLANATION -->
          <section class="prose">
            <h2>Algebraic square vs. square as a shape</h2>
            <p>
              In algebra, the <strong>square of a number</strong> is simply
              \[
                x^2 = x \cdot x.
              \]
              This operation is defined for all real numbers, and negative inputs are perfectly valid:
              for example, \((-3)^2 = 9\).
            </p>
            <p>
              In geometry, a <strong>square</strong> is a polygon with four equal sides and four right
              angles. If its side length is \(s\), then:
            </p>
            <div class="formula-box">
              \[
                A = s^2 \quad \text{(area)}, \qquad
                P = 4s \quad \text{(perimeter)}, \qquad
                d = s\sqrt{2} \quad \text{(diagonal)}.
              \]
            </div>

            <h2>Square geometry formulas in detail</h2>
            <p>
              Suppose you know any one of the four quantities \((s, A, P, d)\). You can recover the others as follows:
            </p>
            <div class="formula-box">
              <strong>From side s</strong><br>
              \[
                A = s^2, \quad P = 4s, \quad d = s\sqrt{2}.
              \]
              <strong>From area A</strong><br>
              \[
                s = \sqrt{A}, \quad P = 4\sqrt{A}, \quad d = \sqrt{2A}.
              \]
              <strong>From perimeter P</strong><br>
              \[
                s = \frac{P}{4}, \quad A = \left(\frac{P}{4}\right)^2, \quad d = \frac{P}{4}\sqrt{2}.
              \]
              <strong>From diagonal d</strong><br>
              \[
                s = \frac{d}{\sqrt{2}}, \quad A = \left(\frac{d}{\sqrt{2}}\right)^2 = \frac{d^2}{2}, \quad P = 4\frac{d}{\sqrt{2}}.
              \]
            </div>

            <h2>Units: from length to area</h2>
            <p>
              If the side is measured in metres, the area is measured in square metres:
              \[
                [s] = \text{m} \quad \Rightarrow \quad [A] = \text{m}^2.
              \]
              The same applies to any unit (centimetres, inches, feet, etc.). The calculator automatically
              keeps the area unit consistent with your choice of length unit.
            </p>

            <h2 id="faq-heading">FAQ – Using the square calculator</h2>

            <h3>Can I use the tool for foundations, slabs, or tiles?</h3>
            <p>
              Yes. If you know the <strong>side</strong> or the <strong>area</strong> of a square footing,
              slab, tile, or panel, the geometry card gives you all derived quantities. For example, if a square tile
              has side 30 cm, the calculator returns an area of 900 cm² (= 0.09 m²) and a diagonal of about 42.43 cm.
            </p>

            <h3>Does the algebraic x² calculator understand units?</h3>
            <p>
              No. The algebraic section treats x as a <strong>dimensionless number</strong>. If you are working
              with physical quantities, use the geometry card so that units are tracked consistently.
            </p>

            <h3>How many decimal places should I keep?</h3>
            <p>
              For engineering and construction, two to three decimals often suffice for lengths in metres
              (e.g. 0.001 m = 1 mm). For academic work, you can switch to 4–6 decimals. The precision
              selector lets you adapt rounding to your context without sacrificing internal accuracy.
            </p>
          </section>

          <!-- JS: CALCULATOR LOGIC -->
          <script>
            (function () {
              // Global precision
              const precisionSelect = document.getElementById('sq-precision');

              function formatNumber(x, opts) {
                if (typeof x !== 'number' || !isFinite(x)) {
                  if (x === Infinity || x === -Infinity) {
                    return (x < 0 ? '-' : '') + 'Infinity';
                  }
                  return 'NaN';
                }

                const mode = precisionSelect.value;
                if (opts && opts.forceInteger) {
                  return String(Math.round(x));
                }

                if (mode === 'auto') {
                  const absx = Math.abs(x);
                  if (absx === 0) return '0';
                  if (absx >= 1e7 || absx < 1e-4) {
                    return x.toExponential(6);
                  }
                  return x.toPrecision(8);
                }

                const d = parseInt(mode, 10);
                if (!isFinite(d)) return x.toString();
                return x.toFixed(d);
              }

              // ---------- Algebraic square ----------
              const algXInput = document.getElementById('alg-x');
              const algCalcBtn = document.getElementById('alg-calc-btn');
              const algError = document.getElementById('alg-error');
              const algResults = document.getElementById('alg-results');
              const algX2El = document.getElementById('alg-x2');
              const algSqrtEl = document.getElementById('alg-sqrtx');
              const algAbsEl = document.getElementById('alg-absx');
              const algNotes = document.getElementById('alg-notes');

              function showAlgError(msg) {
                algError.textContent = msg;
                algError.classList.remove('hidden');
              }
              function hideAlgError() {
                algError.textContent = '';
                algError.classList.add('hidden');
              }

              function computeAlgebraic() {
                hideAlgError();
                algResults.classList.add('hidden');
                algNotes.textContent = '';

                const raw = algXInput.value.trim();
                if (!raw) {
                  showAlgError('Please enter a numeric value for x.');
                  return;
                }

                const normalized = raw.replace(',', '.');
                const x = Number(normalized);
                if (!isFinite(x)) {
                  showAlgError('x must be a finite real number (e.g. 2, -3.5, 1e6).');
                  return;
                }

                const x2 = x * x;
                const absx = Math.abs(x);
                let sqrtx = null;
                let sqrtComment = '';

                if (x < 0) {
                  sqrtComment = 'The real square root is not defined for x &lt; 0. Only x² is shown.';
                } else {
                  sqrtx = Math.sqrt(x);
                }

                algX2El.textContent = formatNumber(x2);
                algAbsEl.textContent = formatNumber(absx);
                if (sqrtx !== null) {
                  algSqrtEl.textContent = formatNumber(sqrtx);
                } else {
                  algSqrtEl.textContent = 'not defined in ℝ (x &lt; 0)';
                }

                const notes = [];
                notes.push('Computed x², √x (when defined), and |x| for x = ' + x + '.');
                if (sqrtComment) notes.push(sqrtComment);
                notes.push('If x carries a physical unit (e.g. m, s), then x² carries the squared unit (e.g. m², s²).');
                algNotes.innerHTML = notes.join(' ');

                algResults.classList.remove('hidden');
              }

              algCalcBtn.addEventListener('click', computeAlgebraic);

              // ---------- Geometry of square ----------
              const geomKnownRadios = document.querySelectorAll('input[name="geom-known"]');
              const geomUnitSelect = document.getElementById('geom-unit');
              const geomValueInput = document.getElementById('geom-value');
              const geomValueLabel = document.getElementById('geom-value-label');
              const geomCalcBtn = document.getElementById('geom-calc-btn');
              const geomExampleBtn = document.getElementById('geom-example-btn');
              const geomClearBtn = document.getElementById('geom-clear-btn');
              const geomError = document.getElementById('geom-error');
              const geomResults = document.getElementById('geom-results');
              const geomSideEl = document.getElementById('geom-side');
              const geomAreaEl = document.getElementById('geom-area');
              const geomPerimeterEl = document.getElementById('geom-perimeter');
              const geomDiagonalEl = document.getElementById('geom-diagonal');
              const geomNotes = document.getElementById('geom-notes');

              function currentKnown() {
                for (const r of geomKnownRadios) {
                  if (r.checked) return r.value;
                }
                return 'side';
              }

              function updateGeomLabel() {
                const k = currentKnown();
                let text = 'Side s';
                if (k === 'area') text = 'Area A';
                else if (k === 'perimeter') text = 'Perimeter P';
                else if (k === 'diagonal') text = 'Diagonal d';
                geomValueLabel.textContent = text;
              }

              geomKnownRadios.forEach(r => {
                r.addEventListener('change', updateGeomLabel);
              });

              function showGeomError(msg) {
                geomError.textContent = msg;
                geomError.classList.remove('hidden');
              }
              function hideGeomError() {
                geomError.textContent = '';
                geomError.classList.add('hidden');
              }

              function unitLabel(u) {
                switch (u) {
                  case 'cm': return 'cm';
                  case 'mm': return 'mm';
                  case 'in': return 'in';
                  case 'ft': return 'ft';
                  default: return 'm';
                }
              }

              function computeGeometry() {
                hideGeomError();
                geomResults.classList.add('hidden');
                geomNotes.textContent = '';

                const k = currentKnown();
                const unit = geomUnitSelect.value;
                const uLabel = unitLabel(unit);
                const raw = geomValueInput.value.trim();
                if (!raw) {
                  showGeomError('Please enter a positive value for the selected quantity.');
                  return;
                }

                const normalized = raw.replace(',', '.');
                const v = Number(normalized);
                if (!isFinite(v) || v <= 0) {
                  showGeomError('The value must be a strictly positive real number.');
                  return;
                }

                let s; // side in chosen unit
                if (k === 'side') {
                  s = v;
                } else if (k === 'area') {
                  s = Math.sqrt(v);
                } else if (k === 'perimeter') {
                  s = v / 4;
                } else if (k === 'diagonal') {
                  s = v / Math.SQRT2;
                } else {
                  showGeomError('Unknown quantity selection.');
                  return;
                }

                if (!isFinite(s) || s <= 0) {
                  showGeomError('The provided value does not correspond to a valid square (check units and magnitude).');
                  return;
                }

                const A = s * s;
                const P = 4 * s;
                const d = s * Math.SQRT2;

                const areaUnit = uLabel + '\u00B2';

                geomSideEl.textContent = formatNumber(s) + ' ' + uLabel;
                geomAreaEl.textContent = formatNumber(A) + ' ' + areaUnit;
                geomPerimeterEl.textContent = formatNumber(P) + ' ' + uLabel;
                geomDiagonalEl.textContent = formatNumber(d) + ' ' + uLabel;

                const notes = [];
                notes.push('Computed square geometry from ' + (k === 'side' ? 'side s' : k) + ' = ' + v + ' ' +
                           (k === 'area' ? areaUnit : uLabel) + '.');
                notes.push('Formulas used: A = s², P = 4s, d = s√2, with all quantities expressed in ' +
                           uLabel + ' (and ' + areaUnit + ' for area).');
                geomNotes.textContent = notes.join(' ');

                geomResults.classList.remove('hidden');
              }

              geomCalcBtn.addEventListener('click', computeGeometry);

              geomExampleBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {
                hideGeomError();
                geomUnitSelect.value = 'm';
                geomValueInput.value = '2';
                geomKnownRadios.forEach(r => {
                  r.checked = (r.value === 'side');
                });
                updateGeomLabel();
                geomResults.classList.add('hidden');
                geomNotes.textContent = '';
              });

              geomClearBtn.addEventListener('click', function () {
                hideGeomError();
                geomValueInput.value = '';
                geomUnitSelect.value = 'm';
                geomKnownRadios.forEach(r => {
                  r.checked = (r.value === 'side');
                });
                updateGeomLabel();
                geomResults.classList.add('hidden');
                geomNotes.textContent = '';
              });

              // Initialize labels
              updateGeomLabel();
            }());
          </script>

